line_1: Th'exhausted mourner mopes, then wildly stalks
line_2: Round the drear dome, and seeks the darkest walks.

line_1: Spreads o'er the heath its slender prickly stalks;
line_2: There shall the grove divide its tepid walks.
Slow, o'er the twilight sands or leafy walks,

line_1: — And now a spotted Pard the lover stalks,
line_2: Plays round her steps, and guards her favour'd walks;

line_1: There the tall pea in stately grandeur stalks,
line_2: And humbler bean midst her own fragrance walks.

line_1: Along the silent room he stalks,
line_2: Looks back and trembles as he walks,
